    ---NOTE: ones that are -1, 0 - 35 are determined by a function where it gets a TextLabel from a global then runs,\
    ---GET_CHARACTER_FROM_AUDIO_CONVERSATION_FILENAME and depending on what the result is it goes in check order of 0 - 9 then A - Z then z (lowercase). So it will then return 0 - 35 or -1 if it's 'z'. The func to handle that ^^ is func_67 in dialog_handler.c atleast in TU27 Xbox360 scripts.\
    ---\
    ---p0 is -1, 0 - 35\
    ---p1 is a char or string (whatever you wanna call it)\
    ---p2 is Global 10597 + i * 6. 'i' is a while(i < 70) loop\
    ---p3 is again -1, 0 - 35 \
    ---p4 is again -1, 0 - 35 \
    ---p5 is either 0 or 1 (bool ?)\
    ---p6 is either 0 or 1 (The func to determine this is bool)\
    ---p7 is either 0 or 1 (The func to determine this is bool)\
    ---p8 is either 0 or 1 (The func to determine this is bool)\
    ---p9 is 0 - 3 (Determined by func_60 in dialogue_handler.c)\
    ---p10 is either 0 or 1 (The func to determine this is bool)\
    ---p11 is either 0 or 1 (The func to determine this is bool)\
    ---p12 is unknown as in TU27 X360 scripts it only goes to p11.
    ---@param index integer
    ---@param p1 string
    ---@param p2 string
    ---@param p3 integer
    ---@param p4 integer
    ---@param p5 BOOL
    ---@param p6 BOOL
    ---@param p7 BOOL
    ---@param p8 BOOL
    ---@param p9 integer
    ---@param p10 BOOL
    ---@param p11 BOOL
    ---@param p12 BOOL
    ADD_LINE_TO_CONVERSATION = function(index, p1, p2, p3, p4, p5, p6, p7, p8, p9, p10, p11, p12) end,

